caption: Great atmosphere
Love this place ! Great atmosphere! Great service
Great atmosphere, great staff, and amazing music. Try the sliders the next time you are there!

I went there for St. Patricks Day weekend and paid over $400 in total to rent one of their private shacks. It was a complete waste of money. I was greeted by an extensive line out of the door that took over 30 minutes, which left a bad taste in my mouth right away. My friends and I got up to the shack and our server brought us one mimosa pitcher. I told her right away we would need more as there were six of us and she might as well bring a few pitchers so she can attend to other tables. She said okay and then for the next 20 minutes I proceeded to see her and all the other servers attending to the people who didn't pay hundreds of dollars and bringing them pitcher after pitcher. I left my seat to go chase her down and let her know we were waiting for a while, were out of drinks, and she then brought a pitcher of beer mixed with mimosas.  Someone who I suppose was the owner or manager came by our shack and asked if he could take pictures for the website and I said sure and told him I had a question. He ignores me. Takes a picture. Then tries to walk off. I yelled excuse me at him and asked him where to food was that was promised per the $400 package. He says the kitchen is backed up and it should be out in a little. Why is your kitchen backed up when you sold these tickets in advance and knew how many people were attending? We then get our food an hour and a half into the event (that is a two hour max, btw) and they only brought 4 plates for 6 friends. When I asked where the other two were, they said they didn't have them.  We received subpar service the rest of the time. As I stated, the servers had no issues serving the tables that didn't pay hundreds of dollars for the most pathetic "VIP" I have ever seen in my entire life. I empathize with servers who are overwhelmed, however, if you want to give good service...try giving your customers solutions rather than excuses. Saying sorry over and over and continuing the poor service made for a terrible experience.  We barely got any drinks. Not enough food for everyone. Bad service. This was my first time going here and I will never be back. I've let others know to avoid this place as well.
Beautiful and fun rooftop vibe. Chill setting with solid food. Jalapeño poppers were my favorite. Best on a nice day but still excellent on a colder or poor weather day.

This was my second time here. The first time i came the service was slow. Gave it another chance and we had a reservation for curling and stayed after for drinks. In the 2 hours we were at our table our waitress came around a total of 3 times. We asked our waitress for the bill and waited about 20 minutes before my friend finally went up to the bar to ask the bartender for our check as her card was already at the bar holding the tab. He was very apologetic which we appreciated. We sat around for another 10-15 minutes waiting for our uber and our waitress walked by us several time and never bothered to apologize or even acknowledge us. I've worked as a server and rarely leave a bad tip but was ready to do so this time. But we couldn't because there was an 18 percent service charge. It's clear that the staff didn't care about giving us good service as they'd be compensated regardless. Definitely won't be back. If you want slow service, over priced drinks, all for a good view then go here.
It's a trendy good time! Could use better beer selections.
Nice place but food is awful. I had one of the worst chicken sandwiches ever. 🚫🧢
Small drinks Alright service Truffle fries were amazing though

Went with my gf for Valentine’s Day, and it was nice, the waiter brung us free drinks for the wait. We had food, and drinks on the rooftop, then went down to the bar for a few more rounds. The bartender downstairs gave us free drinks as well, and the gm came and gave us drink certificates for the next visit. I can see myself going back. Good food, friendly ppl, nice music, and atmosphere.

The rooftop bar is setup quite nicely. The tents are wind proof for the most part and the heaters kinda do their job. But, the drinks were sub par and overpriced. I'd have expected a half decent old fashioned at a place that has whiskey in its name but it was disappointing. And the wait staff treated us like they were doing us a favor. A service fee is included in the bill, so I guess they don't really care about getting a good tip either.
What a fun place, the drinks were par for the course but the fun was the curling and the little love snacks! Thank you!
Great rooftop movie screenings when its not too cold. The menu could use some improvements. Those wings are much too big. Looks steroid injected. The drinks are small and overpriced as well.

We had a curling reservation that we ended up missing because of a wrinkle in our Chicago stay arrangements. Called the staff an hour before our reservation and the manager was extremely friendly and willing to help us out. We ended up missing the reservation but they gave us free drinks in exchange. A great compromise! Super delicious food as well. Thanks Whiskey Business!
Crazy expensive for decent at best drinks. Basically an expensive dive...
Experience was excellent!!!!!

This is my first review on google of any bar/restaurant. Having worked in the service industry myself for a few years i know how difficult it can be, but this was truly a bad experience. My friends and I booked the curling package, which is an hour reservation of the curling lane with a table for 6. We arrived at the curling lane, and then our server almost hilariously placed our QR code on our table, which was covered in 6 inches of snow, along with the stack on chairs that were also covered in snow. Eventually we finally persuaded someone to give us a table inside. We then waited about 25 minutes to be served, after getting the finger treatment multiple times. Finally the bartender seemed to feel bad for us and came to take our orders, after which the server (who gave me the finger treatment about 15 minutes previously) came over and was in disbelief that no one had served us yet, and was then upset that the bartender had gone ahead and done so. No apology or anything for having us wait so long, just glared at us as if we'd done something wrong then begrudgingly took our orders. Overall terrible experience here, won't be returning anytime soon.

Went there for the rooftop igloos for winter/Valentine's day- definitely don't waste your money on this mediocre experience. The igloos are very cold and the heater doesn't really work. They give you a small speaker that most likely won't work (died on us 3x). The drinks are priced waaaaay too high and there is nothing included with your package. You could recreate the same experience and save so much money by sitting on your patio with 6 of your closest friends. The staff is pretty nice though. There is no value to spending so much money to sit in the freezing cold and over pay to drink to be warm.
Friendly staff great vibe

If you’re not careful they will look for anyway they can to upcharge your orders. You know they’ve been caught when you ask about them and they take them off no-questions asked with no explanation. Order more than a couple drinks (which are overpriced and in tiny plastic cups) and you start to just get seltzer water and mixer. Also, waitstaff has no problem being rude and unfriendly because they know no matter what they’re getting that automatic 18% gratuity added to your bill based off their “terms” updated back in August.

Sonya is an amazing manager and Micheal the amount of diligence   he showed in his work is really astounding. Also tori who worked the front door treated me great and was very awesome. Courtney was our server and was amazing! Super attentive and fast. We had her twice for the concert series and movie night. Both experiences were magical. (We just watch Hocus Pocus). We loved having a safe place to go out during covid.

We went last night for the rooftop movie night and it was a good experience!  Our waitress was wonderful, extremely attentive and friendly.  I would definitely recommend going for their movie series, it was worth the $10 ticket. The reason for leaving 3 stars is the drinks are really very expensive for what you get. I got a cocktail that was $13 and it was in a plastic cup smaller than a solo cup and my date got an old fashioned which was $15 and was served in an even smaller plastic cup just a little larger than a dixie cup you'd use for mouthwash. They tasted fine, nothing too spectacular, but, even for Chicago, it felt expensive for such small serving sizes. Overall, I would return but wouldn't order a drink which seems odd for a bar so I'm not sure I'll be back unless it's another special event like the movie series!  In terms of Covid precautions, they were taking temps upon entry & the tables had a decent amount of space between them on the rooftop. I felt safe being there.
Beautiful atmosphere! We had reservations and were seated immediately. Food was also good. Drinks were not impressive, especially the rum drink in the pouch.
This place is awesome
Great food.  Great customer service!! Clean. Good prices

STANDARD BAR FOOD AND DRINKS. UNFORTUNATELY, WE VISITED ON AN EXTREMELY FRIGID DAY SO WE DIDNT GET TO EXPERIENCE THE ROOFTOP BUT THEY HAD A DOPE HOT CHOCOLATE BAR. MUSIC WAS OK.

good ambiance but the bar food sucked! The chicken wings were under cooked so we sent them back the pretzel bites and cheese had no flavor. it looked like they deep fried them they were super thick and oily and doughy not at all like bread.... the drinks were good though.

Came in from out of town to meet up with my brother and his 20 year old daughter headed to college. I walked in at 9:20 and got ID’d walking in. I was puzzled why I was getting carded so early, especially when I was there to eat dinner. I told the door dude that my brother had a daughter who was 20 and was that going to be an issue. He said that she wasn’t allowed in. 9:20 pm and we’re hungry and we were told that we can’t dine in and have dinner and drinks for the old dudes. It’s okay we went down and had dinner and drinks at Texas Roadhouse and spent over $80 buck plus over $20 tip. I’m not sure your concept, but as a Bar Consultant and with over 27 years of experience I don’t understand your concept. Good luck y’all. FYI the door guy was so rude I couldn’t help but write this. Rethink his role.

First off this place always great service. The waiters always smiling, coming back in a timely manner and great with suggestions. I ordered the Impossible Burger and the presentation was good that I was already scarfing it down before I could even get a picture in to post. Now let’s to the drinks, one thing I can say is that they are not shy on the alcohol level lol. I will definitely be back sooner than later.

Had a couple drinks there during a weekday evening and the atmosphere is pretty chill. Usually reservations are recommended (which come with a min. consumption requirement) but if you're there early or are intending to leave before the reservations start (i.e. 8pm), you should be fine getting a table on the very nice roof top. While you don't have much of a view from that rooftop, the setting actually makes you kinda forget that you're in the city with the beach vibe, fake grass carpet and unobstructed view of the sky. Cocktails come in a plastic cup but were still pretty tasty. Temperatures are taken at the entrance and there's plenty of hand sanitizer on the way to your table.
Cool Rummings is my go to summer cocktail in a pouch. Steak nachos are great too!

My friends Hannah and Mitch took us here while we were visiting from Michigan and the food and rooftop were amazing ! Would definitely like to visit again. Staff was extremely friendly.

Great food, great atmosphere and the greatest staff. We had a happy accident that led us to Whiskey Business and now it’s our favorite spot. The avocado toast is excellent and the drinks are strong. 11/10 would eat here again.

Shout out to Mike and Dorian who always make my experience at Whiskey Business top notch!  I hear they have laser shows and movie nights on Tuesday and Thursdays, so be sure to check it out!

The roof top seating is perfect (if your worried about covid) , the food was great i loved the chicken tenders and loaded fries, the staff was really chill.

Be Careful on their reservations..I was lied to and had to pay $50/person as a "deposit" that turned out not to be a deposit. The host told me I would be getting this money back once I arrived, but after we finished eating, I was told I have to use the full $50/person amount or else I could only get a gift card to come back and use. The server ended up racking our tab up with drinks we didn't ask for just to reach the full deposit, and we still had to tip on top of the full deposit we gave. On June 24,2020 my cousin and I had reservations to Whiskey Business on 1367 N. Milwaukee Chicago, IL 60622. We had to pay a $100 reservation fee for 2 people. We didn’t mind because it comes off the bill, so we agreed and booked. I booked our reservation through a website called “Tock”. When I pulled up my cousin mentioned I wonder if security is going to take our temperature to get in. I told him that’s the guidance, he mentioned “Well those white people didn’t get theirs checked as I waited for you”. I told him maybe they went to their car or was already there... give them the benefit of the doubt. We go upstairs and our server Jessica was really nice.  Here is where the problem came... she brings our tab that states $181 and some change. I almost forgot about the $100 reservation deposit we paid as we were having a blast! I mentioned it and she was like her mistake she will get with her manager to take it off. When she came back our tab was $117. I was kind of confused as 181-100=$81. I noticed a 20% gratuity on our bill for a party of 2 people. I asked her why is that on there, Jessica said her manager did that when she added the $100 on there. I told her go get her manager, who name is Sabah (or Savah) by the way... she comes over and states that she added it on there I asked her why. She said because it’s in the email when you book. I had my email and showed her the website I booked through that doesn’t state that. She showed me a different website that do. Like I told her the two systems isn’t communicating to one another. So when I booked that wasn’t on there. She refused to take it off. Then the manager says “Well if servers feels they are going to get a tip we don’t add gratuity unless it’s a group”.  I asked the white couple (next to us who was leaving) did they have gratuity on their bill and they said “NO”.  That sent me over the edge... you mean to tell me you asking your staff to stereotype or discriminate who they think would tip them? Anybody that knows me know I’m a big tipper but that was by far ignorant. I asked Jessica did you not think we would tip you..she mentioned she never heard of that policy before and she kept apologizing. I paid the 20% because the server was nice but she could’ve had more had the manager not  did that. The manager gave so much attitude because I called her out on discriminating and asking your servers to be ignorant.  The GM Sonia came to talk and offer a VIP section and was nice, however I buy sections all the time! This behavior is disgusting and I will NEVER go there again! I’ve never seen somebody add gratuity for a party of 2, especially based on race!!!!
Ok food prices dont match online menu a little more than online
EJ is the best server and manager! Such a great and safe experience post lock down, plus my first time at this place, I will definitely be back. The host was super sweet and courageous as well!!

I loved loved loved this place! We rented the ski lodge on the roof and it was so cozy and fun. We played cards against humanity and an 80s trivia game. Pro tip, if you come when the sun is out, it can get pretty bright and hot in there because of the clear ceiling. Bring sunglasses and lighter clothes!  The food was also really excellent. I got the chicken and waffles during brunch and they were really good. I dock a point because although our server was very good, I didn't get a printed receipt, although I requested one, and I never got a box for my leftovers so I went to the bar to ask for one. Talk about the place that has it all. An all year round rooftop, yoga during the summer's,  and great music (the staff and drinks are the best in the neighborhood)
Great rooftop! Good good, OK service, do it for the vibes

I don't know why this place is getting less than a five-star review.  Recently went here for a private event and had a great time!  We arrived here on a Saturday afternoon at 1pm and the place was packed.  The ground floor level was wall-to-wall people and 80% were women. I don't know if there was a bridal party or a special for females at this time, but it was jam packed.  Our private event was held upstairs outside on the rooftop patio. Definitely a day party vibe.  Our group was under the cute covered Cabanas.  They have some cute pillows made to look like stuffed Whiskey Business T-shirts.  It's a really nice patio, but very crowded.  They had great music playing, and the sound level was perfect for conversations.  There were several events going on at the same time. There was a birthday party, a business group, and a large friend's get together, besides our private event.  To drink we had a One Touch Too Much cocktail (elijah craig small batch, orgeat (almond), pineapple juice, lime juice and angostura) and my favorite, an Electric Lemonade (big machine vodka, lemonade and blue curacao).  Especially refreshing on a hot afternoon.  For food we had a plate of delicious shrimp tacos (grilled shrimp with cilantro lime cabbage slaw served on corn tortillas with chipotle crema) and a plate of steak tacos (skirt steak with onions, cilantro and chihuahua cheese on corn tortillas with chipotle crema).  The Steak Tacos were really good, but, I thought the Shrimp Tacos were excellent.  Check out their Brunch Club on Saturdays and Sundays, as well as their weekly specials.  If you want to sit on the patio, I would suggest making a reservation.If you are looking for great drinks and food in a lively atmosphere, head on over to whiskey business!

My friends and I had a wonderful surprise first time visit here.  We discovered Whiskey Business while eating some tacos across the street.  Loving fries and whiskey we decided to check it out after our meal.  When we walked in, we were blown away by the hype from the Chicago Bulls party crew!  The Chicago Lovabulls we're there and even Benny the Bull!  They gave each if us some nice hats just for walking in and we entered the raffle just for checking in.  After the welcomed surprise when we walked in, we took a seat and began to look over the menu.  Regret set in after we saw all the delicious Fries and other foods we love because we had just stuffed our faces with tacos.  But we order some whiskey drinks and enjoyed the atmosphere.  The three of us all won prizes from the Bulls crew and another friend joined us later for the fun.  My buddy and I to get there cheese and bacon fries so we did and our other friend ordered the Mac and cheese bites.  We all ordered more drinks as well fell in love with our food.  The crowd cleared out as soon as the game was over and since it was getting late and it was what I call a "School Night" since it was a Wednesday and we had work in the morning.  This is a place I hope to frequent more often whenever I come back to visit Chicago.
